        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer899791312" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9689601928432833651">What an interesting book! I usually do not read this genre but thought I&apos;d give this one a shot and loved it. The author moved from point to point smoothly while creating a sense of danger throughout the journey. Beginning with the death of his parents, the main character begins to pursue a new life in Sagrado, New Mexico. From there, the plot and supporting characters bring the whole world to life. I love unpredictable works and this definitely was one. <br/><br/>Readers who like a slight supernatural tw</span>
  <span id="freeText9689601928432833651" style="display:none">What an interesting book! I usually do not read this genre but thought I'd give this one a shot and loved it. The author moved from point to point smoothly while creating a sense of danger throughout the journey. Beginning with the death of his parents, the main character begins to pursue a new life in Sagrado, New Mexico. From there, the plot and supporting characters bring the whole world to life. I love unpredictable works and this definitely was one. <br /><br />Readers who like a slight supernatural twist might like this book as well. It's subtle but does the job right. The author's descriptions also bring me back to my teenage years and the angst I felt during those times. Shane, our main character, experiences are familiar to me, especially the way he must find his way in life and the compassion he shares.<br /><br />I highly recommend Mr. Carrier's work. I bought the paperback and could not put it down!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9689601928432833651" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

